## Specification: Running Agents Tracking & Resizable Board Layout

### 1. Problem Statement

When viewing "All Projects" mode, running agents are not correctly displayed because the panel still filters to the last-selected project instead of showing all running agents. Additionally, the board layout lacks flexibility - users cannot resize the kanban and running agents panels to focus on what they need. The dedicated "Agent Runner" view is redundant and should be integrated into the board view with a collapsible/resizable panel system.

### 2. User Story

As a **developer using DMaker**, I want **the running agents to correctly display in "All Projects" mode and be able to resize/collapse the board panels**, so that **I can monitor all running agents across projects and customize my workspace layout to focus on tasks or agent output**.

### 3. Acceptance Criteria

**Happy Path - Running Agents Tracking:**
- GIVEN I am viewing "All Projects" mode, WHEN there are agents running in multiple projects, THEN I should see ALL running agents in the Running Agents panel (not just one project's agents)
- GIVEN I switch from a specific project to "All Projects", WHEN agents are running, THEN the running agents count should reflect the total across all projects

**Happy Path - Resizable Panels:**
- GIVEN I am on the board view, WHEN I drag the separator between kanban and running agents panel, THEN both panels should resize accordingly
- GIVEN I resize the panels, WHEN I navigate away and return, THEN my panel size preferences should be preserved
- GIVEN I am on the board view, WHEN I click the collapse button on either panel, THEN that panel should collapse fully and I can click to reopen

**Happy Path - Running Agents Dropdown (Top Nav):**
- GIVEN agents are running, WHEN I click the Agents indicator in the top nav bar, THEN a dropdown should appear showing running agents (replacing the dedicated route)

**Edge Cases:**
- GIVEN I collapse a panel to zero width, WHEN I click its toggle button, THEN it should restore to the previous size or default
- GIVEN I am on mobile/tablet, WHEN viewing the board, THEN the resize handles should be hidden and standard collapse behavior should work

**Error Handling:**
- GIVEN a resize operation fails to persist, WHEN I reload the page, THEN reasonable defaults should be applied (35% task panel, 65% kanban)

### 4. Technical Context

| Aspect | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Affected Files | `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx`, `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/running-agents-panel.tsx`, `apps/ui/src/store/app-store.ts`, `apps/ui/src/components/layout/top-nav-bar.tsx`, `apps/ui/src/components/layout/running-agents-indicator.tsx`, `apps/ui/src/routes/__root.tsx` |
| Dependencies | `react-resizable-panels@3.0.6` (already installed) |
| Constraints | Must maintain mobile/tablet responsive behavior, panel sizes must persist across sessions |
| Patterns to Follow | Terminal view uses `react-resizable-panels`, store uses Zustand with persistence |

### 5. Non-Goals

- This feature does NOT include removing the running agents sidebar route completely (it will be kept but de-emphasized)
- This feature does NOT include changing how agents are tracked on the backend
- This feature does NOT include modifying the kanban card sizing or styling

### 6. Implementation Tasks

```tasks
## Phase 1: Fix Running Agents Tracking in All Projects View
- [ ] T001: Update board-view.tsx to pass undefined projectPath when showAllProjects is true | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx
- [ ] T002: Update running-agents-panel.tsx to correctly handle undefined projectPath (show all agents) | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/running-agents-panel.tsx

## Phase 2: Add Resizable Panel System to Board View
- [ ] T003: Add panel size state to app-store (kanbanPanelSize, agentsPanelSize with defaults) | File: apps/ui/src/store/app-store.ts
- [ ] T004: Refactor board-view.tsx to use react-resizable-panels for kanban and agents panel | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx
- [ ] T005: Add resize handle styling with drag indicator and hover states | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx
- [ ] T006: Implement panel collapse/expand toggle buttons on both panels | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx

## Phase 3: Running Agents Dropdown in Top Nav
- [ ] T007: Convert running-agents-indicator to dropdown with agent list | File: apps/ui/src/components/layout/running-agents-indicator.tsx
- [ ] T008: Update top-nav-bar to integrate the running agents dropdown | File: apps/ui/src/components/layout/top-nav-bar.tsx

## Phase 4: Remove Redundant Running Agents Route
- [ ] T009: Remove dedicated running-agents route from navigation | File: apps/ui/src/routes/__root.tsx
- [ ] T010: Delete running-agents-view.tsx component | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/running-agents-view.tsx
```

### 7. Success Metrics

- Running agents panel shows correct agent count when "All Projects" is selected
- Users can drag resize handle to adjust panel widths between 15%-85%
- Panel sizes persist across page reloads and sessions
- Collapse/expand toggles work correctly on both panels
- Mobile/tablet behavior remains functional with standard collapse (no resize handles)
- Running agents dropdown shows in top nav with agent list

### 8. Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| Panel resize may conflict with existing responsive breakpoints | Disable resize handles on tablet/mobile, keep existing collapse behavior |
| Persisted panel sizes may be invalid after code changes | Validate sizes on load, reset to defaults if invalid |
| Performance impact from frequent resize events | Use `onLayout` callback which fires only on resize end |
| User confusion about two collapse modes (toggle vs drag) | Clear visual affordances - drag handle vs collapse button |

